HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 87
By Hemmer
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Ridley Wills II of
Nashville.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly were greatly saddened to learn of
the passing of Ridley Wills II of Nashville; and
WHEREAS, an esteemed community leader, historian, and philanthropist, Ridley Wills II
was a consummate gentleman who worked assiduously to improve the quality of life for his
fellow citizens in numerous capacities; and
WHEREAS, a fifth-generation Nashvillian, Ridley Wills II was a 1956 graduate of
Vanderbilt University, where he was a member of the varsity swim team and served as team
captain; his alma mater meant everything to him, and he was always an enthusiastic supporter
of Vanderbilt athletics; and
WHEREAS, a military veteran, he served as an officer in the United States Navy for two
years before joining National Life and Accident Insurance Company, which was co-founded by
his grandfather, Ridley Wills, Sr., in 1901; and
WHEREAS, in 1976, Mr. Wills was elected to the board of National Life, and he took his
much deserved retirement from the company in 1982, having served as senior vice president;
and
WHEREAS, Mr. Wills then began a new career as a historian and prolific author; he
taught night school classes on local history at Belmont University and Montgomery Bell
Academy and authored thirty-four historical and biographical books about Nashville, Middle
Tennessee, and their notable residents; and
WHEREAS, as a testament to his efforts, Mr. Wills received an Honorary Doctor of
Humane Letters from the University of the South in 2016; and
WHEREAS, a third-generation member of the Board of Trust for Vanderbilt University,
Ridley Wills, together with his wife, Irene, supported Vanderbilt University and Vanderbilt
