University Medical Center through a number of endeavors over the years, including the Wills
Scholarship, to provide assistance to medical students based on financial need, and the Meade
Haven MD/PhD Scholarship, established in 1977 to honor Mr. Wills's father, Jesse E. Wills; and
WHEREAS, a tireless community leader, he served as national chair of the Vanderbilt
University Living Endowment Campaign; chair of the steering committee for the Vanderbilt
Divinity School's endowment campaign; president of the Cumberland Museum and Science
Center; president of the YMCA of Metropolitan Nashville; president of the Tennessee Historical
Society; chair of the Monteagle Sunday School Assembly Endowment Corporation; chair of the
Montgomery Bell Academy Board of Trust; and board member of a number of organizations,
including the National Trust for Historic Preservation; and
WHEREAS, the recipient of numerous honors and accolades for his charitable work, Mr.
Wills received the YMCA's President's Award, the Alexis de Tocqueville Award from the United
Way, the Distinguished Alumnus award from Montgomery Bell Academy, and the Forever
Tennessee Conservation Legacy Award from the Land Trust for Tennessee and was named a
member of the YMCA's Southeast Region Hall of Fame; and
WHEREAS, Ridley Wills was an active and devout member of The Downtown
Presbyterian Church in Nashville, which he served faithfully for many years as a deacon, elder,
and ambassador; and
WHEREAS, deeply devoted to his family, Mr. Wills is survived by his sons, Ridley
(Betsy) Wills III, Morgan (Heather) Wills, Sr., and Tom Wills; his grandchildren, Meade (Cyril) Le
Lay, Ridley (Grayson) Wills IV, Isaac Wills, Jessie Wills, Morgan Wills, Jr., and Laura Jackson
Wills; his brother and sister-in-law, Matt and Judy Wills; and his sister, Ellen Wills Martin; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Wills was preceded in death by his wife, Irene, and their son, Jesse Ely
Wills III; and
WHEREAS, Ridley Wills II leaves behind an indelible legacy of integrity and probity in
public life, compassion and loyalty in private life, and diligence and dedication in all his chosen
endeavors; and
